main event: An object was observed on radar in Greenham Common, England on September 26, 1960.
interesting points: The object was tracked moving at a ground speed of over 200 knots., The elevation angle of the object was between 80° and 85°., The duration of the observation was 5 minutes., The sighting was reported to the RAF Maintenance Unit at Greenham Common., The radar return indicated characteristics similar to an air-breathing jet aircraft.
witness description: The observation was made via ground radar and no eyewitness accounts are mentioned.
